com.microfocus.adm.pulse.pluginapi.chain.dto

Interface PulseChange


  • public interface PulseChange

    Describes one change that makes up the changeset. This can be used to work out what the changes that make up a changeset and can be used by an expert to locate the files that may be of interest. Some experts will just be interested in every file in the workspace but others may limit themselves to the files that have changed.

    Since:
    CM_14.2

      • isDirectory

        boolean isDirectory()

        Get a flag that indicates whether the change represents a change to a directory.

        Returns:
        True if the change is about a directory.

      • getType

        PulseChange.ChangeType getType()

        Get the kind of modification this change represents. This can never be null.

        Returns:
        Type of change that was made.
        Since:
        CM_14.2

      • getPathBefore

        String getPathBefore()

        Get the path of the item that was changed before the change was carried out. Will be null if the change type is PulseChange.ChangeType.ADDED or PulseChange.ChangeType.MODIFIED. This value is for informational purposes and shouldn't be used to locate the item in the changeset workspace.

        Returns:
        Path of the item before the change.
        Since:
        CM_14.2

      • getPathAfter

        String getPathAfter()

        Get the path after the change. This can be used to locate the file content in the workspace by appending it to the directory returned by PulseChangeset.getDirectory(). Will be null if the change type is PulseChange.ChangeType.REMOVED.

        Returns:
        Path of the item after the change.
        Since:
        CM_14.2
